[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring dependency access in Gradle**\n\nI’m considering whether javac can access transitive dependency classes in Gradle when using testImplementation for a primary dependency. With Maven, runtime dependencies compile, but not if they're in test scope. There's a concern around missing javax.inject for potential native-image builds. I wonder if we should add javax.inject and sisu, especially since test classes might not include class annotations. Also, Graal native-image analysis seems tricky due to annotation loading. Adding testImplementation for javax.inject might be necessary if the provided dependency isn't transitive.\n\n**Assessing test dependencies in Gradle**\n\nI'm looking at the sec-dispatcher, which has a provided javax.inject in its POM, and I'm considering adding a testImplementation for javax.inject if needed. Since the library relies on provided annotations and test classes instantiate those implementations, it seems appropriate to add the right test dependency. There’s no need for sisu because source imports `javax.inject.*`. I’ll make sure not to pin the version and confirm that I’m correctly editing the build.gradle to reflect these changes.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_025682ae0386bd27016a0ba633323881a09b62e40368c73f25\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqC6Y7XfoHTXaW29loN_cRYWN-uRFWHR3JcY-BkALrwTypcQ5McqR6PrzmpleODwiwpLfsSawfM7Jf8zd_8KtN5wTplz3v2jLEdoLZ06XYwPW1A3Eip4hwpQh9TcT5xv1K_WQRuu12v3Iu8QGJu0cL3fJfmL0IducPaF7ZMSoPDhYmEkgwS9cW9I2Gxcqf9TH3GvlBqiPgGGvXMmLMivHsN-O8MrE1sQfhFBnq-7gpfhFWP_i4VNNM5Ktj_87M_1NGZgGQsQCdz0LRnse8oqJZcAsEBQg3EUAF5y9rnmsvMeMAtCaR-mOCspPY-_lP-Lf7gQNEG8j9QldhK83FNyqupnv0Z1z6ClvkazR83qk0aVbBjpEUYkrzfV5Iai4Tb9gIOpMROyELF8UHIx0H9y5j3Fir3VhopNLJMe928iYgt5Wp1BlvTj7VDLPlRKUrvUGMQkOtfrBfR48MSbTTv9AMSBgJyJSSY0FLDQgG0uls-omHyWJD2TRVJwMCbydxdZJeN146tS_YYhTZuPxwvxH-9hgGdJZchALnfZuoo3gq4JBCSWBqWJPRC